pixz
------------------------------------------
Pixz (pronounced 'pixie') is a parallel, indexing version of XZ

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libarchive13-3.8.7-1
  liblzma5-5.8.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  asciidoc-10.2.0-1
  autoconf-15-3
  autoconf-archive-2024.10.16-1
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.46-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  libarchive-devel-3.8.7-1
  liblzma-devel-5.8.3-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/vasi/pixz

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/vasi/pixz/archive/refs/tags/v1.0.7.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack pixz-1.0.7-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./pixz-1.0.7-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/pixz-1.0.7-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/pixz-1.0.7-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(pixz)
  /usr/bin/pixz.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/pixz.README
  /usr/share/doc/pixz/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/pixz/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/pixz/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/pixz/TODO
  /usr/share/man/man1/pixz.1.gz

